1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,620
[Hokong Maximum Security Prison]

2
00:00:02,960 --> 00:00:03,890
I never thought

3
00:00:04,550 --> 00:00:05,850
Mr. Hon could actually come out.

4
00:00:06,440 --> 00:00:08,490
Medical parole isn't real freedom.

5
00:00:09,910 --> 00:00:10,700
Let's keep a low profile

6
00:00:11,240 --> 00:00:12,010
and not cause trouble.

7
00:00:21,860 --> 00:00:23,340
[Hokong Maximum Security Prison]

8
00:00:27,030 --> 00:00:27,810
Follow them to the hospital.

9
00:00:36,710 --> 00:00:38,010
While on medical parole,

10
00:00:38,320 --> 00:00:40,010
you are forbidden from engaging
in any illegal or disciplinary conduct,

11
00:00:40,030 --> 00:00:42,690
leaving or changing
the designated hospital,

12
00:00:42,710 --> 00:00:44,980
or engaging in activities
unrelated to your medical treatment.

13
00:00:45,320 --> 00:00:47,330
If any of these violations are found,

14
00:00:47,350 --> 00:00:48,690
the medical parole
will be immediately terminated,

15
00:00:49,030 --> 00:00:50,940
and you'll be immediately remanded
to prison.

16
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:54,180
Lung.

17
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:03,010
You...

18
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:04,490
How did you pull this off?

19
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,020
Did I scare you?

20
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:11,490
They were watching too closely.

21
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:13,290
If the act was too weak,

22
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:14,900
I wouldn't have made it through.

23
00:01:15,590 --> 00:01:17,570
So I was the only one who didn't know.

24
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:19,490
Lit, you must have known.

25
00:01:19,510 --> 00:01:20,770
Whether I know or not isn't important.

26
00:01:21,040 --> 00:01:21,740
All that matters

27
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:23,100
is that Dad gets out.

28
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:25,210
Lit.

29
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:27,410
You've put in a lot of effort.

30
00:01:27,790 --> 00:01:29,570
Stay in touch with Mr. Ong,

31
00:01:30,230 --> 00:01:31,330
as I can't leave right now.

32
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:32,900
Dad, don't worry.

33
00:01:33,150 --> 00:01:34,290
Just focus on getting some rest

34
00:01:34,310 --> 00:01:35,540
and recovering.

35
00:01:38,310 --> 00:01:38,900
Come on.

36
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:42,490
Mr. Hon, you're

37
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:43,690
back to your best.

38
00:01:45,310 --> 00:01:47,180
How could I be like before?

39
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:51,130
I might be able to fool everyone else,

40
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:52,980
but not myself.

41
00:01:58,590 --> 00:01:59,180
How are you holding up?

42
00:01:59,200 --> 00:01:59,930
Hello?

43
00:02:02,070 --> 00:02:02,570
Sir,

44
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:04,210
Mr. Fung is here.

45
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:05,620
He brought flowers

46
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:07,540
and says he's visiting
on behalf of Mr. Ong.

47
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:10,170
I'm not seeing him.

48
00:02:10,430 --> 00:02:10,890
Yes.

49
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,220
I'll handle it.

50
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:13,340
Dad.

51
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:18,610
Lung,

52
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:21,100
you can count on Lit.

53
00:02:22,150 --> 00:02:23,730
He used to follow your every word.

54
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:25,500
Now he's grown up

55
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:27,130
and knows the meaning of responsibility.

56
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,410
You really ought to get some more rest.

57
00:03:56,830 --> 00:04:02,480
[Justice Is Mine]

58
00:04:02,980 --> 00:04:05,580
[Episode 17]

59
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:12,730
You're very punctual.

60
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,730
You come here for coffee

61
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:15,780
exactly at 1:15 PM every day.

62
00:04:18,630 --> 00:04:19,780
Hon Fui-lung is out.

63
00:04:20,190 --> 00:04:21,050
That shouldn't be news to you.

64
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:23,490
After all, you approved
his medical parole.

65
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:25,250
Also,

66
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:27,100
you ruled against the old town

67
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:28,410
in the land deed case,

68
00:04:29,270 --> 00:04:30,850
and you officially deemed
Sek Chi-yeung a corrupt officer.

69
00:04:32,830 --> 00:04:34,460
You never would have made
these rulings before.

70
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,460
But now, you are completely different.

71
00:04:39,190 --> 00:04:41,370
I ruled based on the evidence
presented in court.

72
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:43,610
It's the same for any case.

73
00:04:44,070 --> 00:04:45,290
If you have new evidence,

74
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:46,700
you can appeal.

75
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,900
I've read the A05 statement.

76
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:51,540
There's not enough evidence to appeal.

77
00:04:52,310 --> 00:04:53,340
Just wait a little longer.

78
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:56,900
Maybe things

79
00:04:57,310 --> 00:04:58,580
will turn out differently.

80
00:04:59,270 --> 00:05:00,980
It takes time to set things right, huh?

81
00:05:06,870 --> 00:05:07,460
I've got to go.

82
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,100
Me too.

83
00:05:10,870 --> 00:05:11,930
I need to go back and investigate

84
00:05:12,510 --> 00:05:14,340
why the murderer of Sek Chi-yeung

85
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:15,580
confessed to killing Hon Gong.

86
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:18,290
Why are two obviously unrelated cases

87
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,020
tied together?

88
00:05:25,260 --> 00:05:30,740
[Coffee Alley]

89
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:32,580
Losing the lawsuit

90
00:05:33,390 --> 00:05:35,100
is a great pity.

91
00:05:35,870 --> 00:05:37,100
[Villagers' Representative Assembly]
But we also have to accept

92
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,410
the fact of selling the land.

93
00:05:38,830 --> 00:05:39,850
Where's Uncle Chen?

94
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:41,290
What's his take on this?

95
00:05:41,310 --> 00:05:42,490
He fell ill

96
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:43,900
due to the land deed issue.

97
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:46,290
Leave him be.

98
00:05:46,830 --> 00:05:47,540
The developer

99
00:05:47,830 --> 00:05:48,930
will be here the day after tomorrow.

100
00:05:49,510 --> 00:05:50,460
We're running

101
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:51,660
out of time.

102
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,290
Why don't we just not let them in?

103
00:05:53,630 --> 00:05:54,340
Exactly.

104
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:55,700
If they come for the land,

105
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:57,610
we'll fight to the bitter end!

106
00:05:57,630 --> 00:05:58,610
- Right!
- Right!

107
00:05:58,630 --> 00:06:00,020
- We'll fight them to the death!
- No backing down!

108
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,220
We'll stand our ground!

109
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,610
- To the end!
- Till the last breath!

110
00:06:02,630 --> 00:06:03,810
- We won't let them take it!
- We won't let them take it!

111
00:06:05,750 --> 00:06:07,100
Hon Fui-lung is out on medical parole.

112
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:10,780
With the councilor watching,

113
00:06:10,950 --> 00:06:12,460
Hon Lit won't dare to mess around.

114
00:06:12,830 --> 00:06:14,220
But we still need to be ready.

115
00:06:15,270 --> 00:06:16,900
Even if we screw things up ourselves,

116
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:18,490
we can't let outsiders step in.

117
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:19,700
Understood.

118
00:06:20,980 --> 00:06:22,700
Chi, why don't you say something?

119
00:06:26,740 --> 00:06:27,610
We'll fight till the very end!

120
00:06:27,660 --> 00:06:28,410
Everyone.

121
00:06:30,340 --> 00:06:31,420
I'll keep it brief.

122
00:06:32,260 --> 00:06:33,900
They are playing dirty together,

123
00:06:34,540 --> 00:06:36,260
so we must stand united.

124
00:06:37,460 --> 00:06:39,620
We lost the land deed lawsuit.

125
00:06:39,620 --> 00:06:41,300
And one of our own ended up in prison.

126
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:43,580
But we still have leverage.

127
00:06:43,940 --> 00:06:46,100
This isn't over yet.

128
00:06:46,700 --> 00:06:48,180
We must stand together.

129
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:49,940
No more separate deals.

130
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:52,100
We negotiate as one.

131
00:06:52,540 --> 00:06:54,540
If you all trust me,

132
00:06:54,740 --> 00:06:56,500
I'll take the lead
in talks with the developer.

133
00:06:56,940 --> 00:06:57,740
Chi,

134
00:06:58,500 --> 00:06:59,780
you're betraying the old town.

135
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:00,740
That's right.

136
00:07:01,660 --> 00:07:03,580
I swear, in front of everyone here,

137
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:06,260
if you choose to hold out till the end,

138
00:07:06,700 --> 00:07:07,940
when the developer shows up,

139
00:07:07,940 --> 00:07:09,500
I will let them tear down

140
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:10,340
my own house first.

141
00:07:12,340 --> 00:07:14,220
Not only will I stand on the front line,

142
00:07:15,060 --> 00:07:16,220
I'll guard it to the very end.

143
00:07:17,340 --> 00:07:19,420
If we win this fight,

144
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:21,220
we won't just get the best deal,

145
00:07:21,740 --> 00:07:22,620
but we'll have a say

146
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:25,740
in shaping the future of the old town.

147
00:07:26,660 --> 00:07:27,820
As long as we're here,

148
00:07:28,220 --> 00:07:30,500
we'll have a stake in the old town.

149
00:07:31,380 --> 00:07:32,100
I agree with Chi.

150
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:33,940
Me too.

151
00:07:33,940 --> 00:07:34,740
Ditto.

152
00:07:34,740 --> 00:07:35,620
If they want to take it,

153
00:07:35,860 --> 00:07:37,180
fine, let them.

154
00:07:37,460 --> 00:07:38,580
But this land

155
00:07:38,820 --> 00:07:40,620
was passed down to us.

156
00:07:40,620 --> 00:07:41,940
I'd rather die than sell it!

157
00:07:42,340 --> 00:07:43,500
We won't sell!

158
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:46,460
- No selling!
- No way we're selling!

159
00:07:46,460 --> 00:07:47,740
Let's all take a breath.

160
00:07:47,740 --> 00:07:48,660
- No sale!
- No selling!

161
00:07:48,660 --> 00:07:49,420
Let's stay calm, folks.

162
00:07:49,420 --> 00:07:50,420
Take your time.

163
00:07:51,220 --> 00:07:52,540
Let them get it off their chest.

164
00:07:53,140 --> 00:07:54,340
If they don't, they'll stay bitter.

165
00:07:54,340 --> 00:07:55,980
Once it's out, they'll back down.

166
00:07:56,100 --> 00:08:00,860
- We're not selling!
- Not for any price!

167
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:02,140
Absolutely no selling!

168
00:08:02,140 --> 00:08:04,340
- I'd rather die than sell this land!
- No selling!

169
00:08:08,820 --> 00:08:09,500
Hon Lit speaking.

170
00:08:09,860 --> 00:08:12,020
Your dad gave Mr. Fung
the cold shoulder.

171
00:08:12,020 --> 00:08:13,700
Your attitude is pure disrespect.

172
00:08:15,060 --> 00:08:16,580
My respect doesn't put food
on your table.

173
00:08:17,660 --> 00:08:19,180
I'm afraid that if your father

174
00:08:19,420 --> 00:08:20,220
is upset,

175
00:08:20,220 --> 00:08:21,620
there's no telling
what foolish thing he might do.

176
00:08:22,140 --> 00:08:23,260
Don't worry.

177
00:08:24,060 --> 00:08:25,580
I won't let him be upset.

178
00:08:25,820 --> 00:08:26,340
Alright.

179
00:08:27,100 --> 00:08:28,860
That's what I needed to hear.

180
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:44,700
Dad,

181
00:08:45,420 --> 00:08:46,900
I picked up

182
00:08:47,860 --> 00:08:49,260
your favorite eight treasure duck.

183
00:08:51,780 --> 00:08:53,820
Lum will bring some food later.

184
00:08:54,540 --> 00:08:55,780
She said she wasn't feeling well,

185
00:08:55,780 --> 00:08:56,740
so she won't be coming today.

186
00:08:58,060 --> 00:08:58,860
Is she alright?

187
00:08:58,860 --> 00:08:59,460
I don't know the details,

188
00:09:00,060 --> 00:09:01,340
but it's probably nothing serious.

189
00:09:01,860 --> 00:09:03,540
She told me to get you anything

190
00:09:03,540 --> 00:09:04,100
you want to eat.

191
00:09:04,460 --> 00:09:05,740
I've bought it.

192
00:09:06,060 --> 00:09:07,020
Just go grab a meal.

193
00:09:07,340 --> 00:09:08,180
I'll keep him company.

194
00:09:09,740 --> 00:09:10,380
Dad,

195
00:09:10,620 --> 00:09:11,420
this duck

196
00:09:11,420 --> 00:09:12,300
is from the restaurant where you took me

197
00:09:12,300 --> 00:09:13,780
and my brother to eat when we were kids.

198
00:09:14,260 --> 00:09:15,500
It was called Fooklam.

199
00:09:15,740 --> 00:09:16,340
Do you remember?

200
00:09:17,820 --> 00:09:19,020
I was even afraid it would sell out,

201
00:09:19,020 --> 00:09:20,260
so I ordered it two days in advance.

202
00:09:20,940 --> 00:09:21,420
Come on,

203
00:09:21,740 --> 00:09:22,380
dig in while it's still warm.

204
00:09:41,940 --> 00:09:43,180
Today, we're

205
00:09:43,580 --> 00:09:45,260
skipping the wine and brandy.

206
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:46,980
Let's grab some beer

207
00:09:47,260 --> 00:09:48,260
and take it easy.

208
00:10:15,500 --> 00:10:16,500
Dad,

209
00:10:17,580 --> 00:10:18,380
actually,

210
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:20,060
with the Uncles holding down the fort,

211
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:22,940
we're untouchable in the drug game.

212
00:10:23,940 --> 00:10:25,660
Casino commissions
bring in serious profit,

213
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:27,980
especially the loan-sharking side.

214
00:10:27,980 --> 00:10:29,220
I've carved it out as its own operation.

215
00:10:29,980 --> 00:10:31,740
The future development of the old town

216
00:10:32,180 --> 00:10:33,420
is our opportunity to shift

217
00:10:33,420 --> 00:10:35,460
the Hon family's business
from illegal to legal.

218
00:10:35,860 --> 00:10:37,140
That place is set to become

219
00:10:37,140 --> 00:10:38,580
the next tourism and gambling hotspot.

220
00:10:38,980 --> 00:10:40,180
If we don't fight for it,

221
00:10:40,180 --> 00:10:41,380
the old town will take it all.

222
00:10:53,660 --> 00:10:54,580
Thank you, Dad.

223
00:11:00,860 --> 00:11:02,020
Actually, Gong's matter

224
00:11:02,860 --> 00:11:04,140
has always been on my mind.

225
00:11:04,940 --> 00:11:05,780
I will

226
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:07,820
most certainly avenge him.

227
00:11:37,620 --> 00:11:38,540
Are you Tong Huen?

228
00:11:40,380 --> 00:11:41,140
Sektau...

229
00:11:43,020 --> 00:11:44,740
We've always called him that
since we were kids.

230
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:46,660
I know you're his girlfriend.

231
00:11:47,300 --> 00:11:48,660
He showed me your picture

232
00:11:48,660 --> 00:11:49,620
and mentioned you before.

233
00:11:52,580 --> 00:11:53,380
I'm Lum Chin.

234
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:54,740
I know.

235
00:11:55,140 --> 00:11:56,500
He told me about you.

236
00:11:58,100 --> 00:11:59,020
May I

237
00:11:59,020 --> 00:11:59,940
offer incense to Sektau?

238
00:12:04,860 --> 00:12:07,940
[In Memory of Sek Chi-yeung]

239
00:12:13,620 --> 00:12:14,740
I hope one day

240
00:12:15,140 --> 00:12:16,940
I can send him back
to the police cemetery.

241
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:20,100
I don't believe
Sektau was a rotten police officer.

242
00:12:21,060 --> 00:12:21,740
Yes,

243
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:23,500
he helped the police

244
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:24,420
relay messages to Lung.

245
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:25,860
But I know

246
00:12:26,260 --> 00:12:27,700
he never took Lung's money.

247
00:12:27,940 --> 00:12:29,260
He was framed.

248
00:12:30,220 --> 00:12:31,220
While investigating the arson,

249
00:12:31,340 --> 00:12:32,900
he uncovered some untouchable secrets.

250
00:12:33,740 --> 00:12:34,940
He found out that the killer

251
00:12:34,940 --> 00:12:36,060
was just a scapegoat.

252
00:12:39,460 --> 00:12:40,180
Something is off

253
00:12:40,300 --> 00:12:41,300
with the case.

254
00:12:42,820 --> 00:12:44,140
Now that Chi-yeung is dead,

255
00:12:44,820 --> 00:12:46,140
all leads are gone.

256
00:12:48,060 --> 00:12:49,940
[Sek Chi-yeung. Tat Ga-ma. Lau Mao]
No wonder he kept looking for Lau Mao.

257
00:12:51,740 --> 00:12:53,020
I told him

258
00:12:53,660 --> 00:12:55,500
that Lau Mao told others
he had seen the real killer.

259
00:12:57,540 --> 00:12:58,740
I always believed the murderer

260
00:12:58,740 --> 00:13:00,020
had already been locked up

261
00:13:00,340 --> 00:13:00,940
and was dead.

262
00:13:02,420 --> 00:13:03,860
The killer is still at large.

263
00:13:05,260 --> 00:13:06,820
[Tall Man. Wrong guy. Scapegoat]
Sektau died

264
00:13:07,020 --> 00:13:08,100
trying to find the real killer.

265
00:13:09,340 --> 00:13:09,900
Oh, right.

266
00:13:10,180 --> 00:13:11,460
Is there anything I can do to help?

267
00:13:13,020 --> 00:13:14,140
Not unless you happen to have seen

268
00:13:14,780 --> 00:13:15,980
the actual killer from two decades ago.

269
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:18,780
What were the features of that killer?

270
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:20,340
All we know

271
00:13:20,860 --> 00:13:22,500
is he was tall

272
00:13:22,780 --> 00:13:23,660
and had a scar

273
00:13:23,660 --> 00:13:25,660
like an earthworm on his right shoulder.

274
00:13:28,740 --> 00:13:30,940
[Unknown face, tall build]

275
00:13:30,940 --> 00:13:32,780
[Earthworm-shaped scar
on his right shoulder]

276
00:13:41,860 --> 00:13:42,620
Anyway,

277
00:13:43,540 --> 00:13:44,500
thank you for coming

278
00:13:44,860 --> 00:13:45,620
to visit Chi-yeung.

279
00:13:47,620 --> 00:13:48,780
I am Hon Fui-lung's woman.

280
00:13:49,540 --> 00:13:51,060
You and Sektau didn't look down on me,

281
00:13:51,820 --> 00:13:52,700
so I should be thanking you.

282
00:14:05,140 --> 00:14:06,500
Chun Yue is responsible
for Gong's death,

283
00:14:07,700 --> 00:14:08,940
